{"title_page": "1999\u20132000 FC Barcelona season", "text_new": "{{Infobox Football club season\n| club           = [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]]\n| season         = 1999-2000\n| manager        = [[Louis van Gaal]]\n| mgrtitle       = Head Coach\n| chrtitle       = President\n| chairman       = [[Josep Llu\u00eds N\u00fa\u00f1ez]]\n| stadium        = [[Camp Nou]]\n| league         = [[La Liga]]\n| league result  = [[1999\u20132000 La Liga|2nd]]\n| cup1           = [[Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a]]\n| cup1 result    = [[1999 Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a|Runners-up]]\n| cup2           = [[Copa del Rey]]\n| cup2 result    = [[1999\u20132000 Copa del Rey#Semifinals|Semi-finals]]\n| cup3           = [[UEFA Champions League]]\n| cup3 result    = [[1999\u20132000 UEFA Champions League#Semi-finals|Semi-finals]]\n| league topscorer    = <br>[[Patrick Kluivert]] (15)\n| season topscorer    = <br>[[Patrick Kluivert]]<br>[[Rivaldo]] (23)\n  | pattern_la1= _barca9900h\n  |pattern_b1=_barca9900h\n  |pattern_ra1=_barca9900h\n  | pattern_sh1= _barcelona9801\n  |pattern_so1=_barca9900h\n  | leftarm1= 000025 |body1= 000025 |rightarm1= 000025 |shorts1= 000025 |socks1= 000025 \n  | pattern_la2=_barca0001a\n  |pattern_b2=_barca0001a\n  |pattern_ra2=_barca0001a\n  | pattern_sh2= _barcelona9801  |pattern_so2=_barca9900h\n  | leftarm2= 203b5a |body2= 203b5a |rightarm2= 203b5a |shorts2= 000025 |socks2= 000025 |\n  | prevseason = [[1998\u201399 FC Barcelona season|1998\u201399]]\n  | nextseason = [[2000\u201301 FC Barcelona season|2000\u201301]]\n}}\n'''[[FC Barcelona]]''' did not repeat its successful season in 1998\u201399, and fell back to second in [[La Liga]], as well as knocked out of the Champions League in the semi-finals.\n\nBarcelona did not perform well in the mid season and lost the league title to [[Deportivo La Coru\u00f1a]] just 5 points behind and [[Louis van Gaal]] was let go by the club, with former [[Real Betis]] coach [[Lorenzo Serra Ferrer]] taking over after 1999-2000 season.\n\nDespite trophyless season, the side managed to reach the semi-finals of the [[UEFA Champions League]], where it lost to eventual competition runners up [[Valencia CF|Valencia]].\n\n==Squad==\n:''Squad at end of season''<ref>http://www.footballsquads.co.uk/spain/1999-2000/laliga/barce.htm</ref>\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no=1|nat=NED|pos=GK|name=[[Ruud Hesp]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=2|nat=NED|pos=DF|name=[[Michael Reiziger]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=3|nat=FRA|pos=DF|name=[[Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric D\u00e9hu]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=4|nat=ESP|pos=MF|name=[[Pep Guardiola|Josep Guardiola]]|other=[[Captain (association football)|captain]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=5|nat=ESP|pos=DF|name=[[Abelardo Fern\u00e1ndez]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=6|nat=NED|pos=MF|name=[[Ronald de Boer]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=7|nat=POR|pos=MF|name=[[Lu\u00eds Figo]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=8|nat=NED|pos=MF|name=[[Phillip Cocu]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=9|nat=NED|pos=FW|name=[[Patrick Kluivert]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=10|nat=FIN|pos=MF|name=[[Jari Litmanen]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=11|nat=BRA|pos=MF|name=[[Rivaldo]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=12|nat=ESP|pos=DF|name=[[Sergi Barju\u00e1n]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=14|nat=NGA|pos=MF|name=[[Emmanuel Amunike]]}}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|no=17|nat=NED|pos=DF|name=[[Winston Bogarde]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=19|nat=ESP|pos=FW|name=[[Dani Garc\u00eda (footballer, born 1974)|Dani Garc\u00eda]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=20|nat=POR|pos=MF|name=[[Sim\u00e3o Sabrosa]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=21|nat=ESP|pos=MF|name=[[Luis Enrique (footballer)|Luis Enrique]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=22|nat=NED|pos=DF|name=[[Frank de Boer]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=23|nat=NED|pos=MF|name=[[Boudewijn Zenden]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=25|nat=ESP|pos=GK|name=[[Francesc Arnau]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=26|nat=ESP|pos=MF|name=[[Xavi|Xavi Hern\u00e1ndez]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=28|nat=ESP|pos=MF|name=[[Gabri Garc\u00eda]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=29|nat=ESP|pos=MF|name=[[Mario Rosas]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=31|nat=ESP|pos=MF|name=[[Nano (Spanish footballer, born 1982)|Nano]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=32|nat=ESP|pos=DF|name=[[Carles Puyol]]}}